					<![CDATA[
						 <p><em>I'm starting with the man in the mirror<br /> I'm asking him to change his ways</em></p> <p>Big shout-out to scpcrnp, who helped me a lot with fleshing out all the ideas here. Other people from chat/forums who gave feedback, in no particular order: Captain Kirby, amnestic_protocol, AquaBlack, and Zyn.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Image&nbsp;credits</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Image&nbsp;credits</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p><br /> Header image is originally from here and photoshopped by me: <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/irreversibility/8809163449/in/photostream/">https://www.flickr.com/photos/irreversibility/8809163449/in/photostream/</a> - &quot;Man In The Mirror&quot; by Flickr user Irreversibility.</p> <p>The mugshots at the end are from this NIST dataset: <a href="https://www.nist.gov/srd/nist-special-database-18">https://www.nist.gov/srd/nist-special-database-18</a> - filenames are 00173_1_F.png and 00173_1_L.png if you want to check. Any media released by the federal government is public domain by default (NIST confirms: <a href="https://www.nist.gov/disclaimer">https://www.nist.gov/disclaimer</a>) so no issue there.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
